GateDocument.TextWithNodes: They can be bleak and eerie, often very exposed, often covered with antiquities like bronze age burial mounds, stone circles and settlements -- until late in the bronze age they were rich farmlands, then a change in the climate caused the skies to cloud over and rain to wash the goodness from the soil.
